OCP states classes should be open for extension but closed for modification. Bad: A ReportGenerator with if/elif for each report type — adding a new type requires modifying the class. Good: Create an abstract ReportType class, then extend it with ConcreteReport, PDFReport, HTMLReport, etc. The generator uses the abstract interface, so new types don't require modification. Example:
```python
# Bad
class ReportGenerator:
    def generate(self, type_):
        if type_ == 'pdf': ...
        elif type_ == 'html': ...
        # Adding 'excel' requires modifying this

# Good
class Report(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def generate(self): pass

class PDFReport(Report):
    def generate(self): pass

class ReportGenerator:
    def generate(self, report: Report):
        report.generate()  # Works for any report
```
